definition: first thing in the morning/at daybreak
Qing or Ch'ing dynasty of imperial China (1644-1911)/surname Qing
clear/distinct/quiet/just and honest/pure/to settle or clear up/to clean up or purge

sentences.english: And when the morning arose, they were sent away with their asses.
sentences.chinese: 清早天一發亮，就遣送這些人帶着他們的驢走了。

sentences.english: They sallied forth early in the morning.
I remild paind Beijing early in the morning.
Gossip girl: I bet you’re wondering what gossip girl is doing up so early.
sentences.chinese: 我敢肯定你們都在疑惑緋聞少女大清早的在幹嗎。

sentences.english: His coup of early this morning had been reported.
sentences.chinese: 他今天一清早乾的好事已經報案了。

sentences.english: Very early next morning Jaimie heard the noise again.
sentences.chinese: 接下來的早上，一大清早，傑米又聽到了那個聲音。

sentences.english: He took the nutriment eagerly, to he get eaten nothing since dawn.
sentences.chinese: 他狼吞虎嚥地喫，應該他從清早起什麼也沒喫。

sentences.english: The next morning when I opened the window I was astonished to find out what a grand mountain.
sentences.chinese: 第二天清早推窗，才一驚，好一座大山，堵着天。

sentences.english: She set out in the early morning from Wuchang but did not arrive at my home after two and half an hour.
sentences.chinese: 她清早就從武昌出發，兩個半小時還沒有到我家。

sentences.english: He is hasl set for an early on morning start.
sentences.chinese: 他已做好清早出發的一切準備。

sentences.english: What, eventually, will become of us who so quickly grow lukewarm?
sentences.chinese: 我們一清早，就這樣冷淡，後來更將怎樣呢？

sentences.english: Family waiting for train early in the morning in a station before Bodhgaya.
sentences.chinese: 快要到達菩提伽耶的前一站，清早就很多人在等車。

sentences.english: At nine in the morning there passed a church.
Fans began lining up early in the morning to buy their cup - tie tickets.
sentences.chinese: 球迷大清早就開始排隊，等着買優勝杯決賽的入場券。

sentences.english: And all the people came early in the morning to him in the temple, for to hear him.
sentences.chinese: 衆百姓清早上聖殿，到耶穌那裏，要聽他講道。

sentences.english: He set off early in the morning with the breakfast untouched.
sentences.chinese: 他一清早就走了，早飯一動也沒動。
